  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1987-05-01", 
    "text": "Amends the Federal criminal code to make it unlawful for an employer to monitor an employee's work phone call unless a repeating audible warning tone is utilized. Allows any person whose call is monitored in violation of this Act to recover civil damages."
